initial statement:
 1042
Your Honor,

I stand before this court today to plead guilty to the offense of TV licence payment evasion. I take full responsibility for my actions and I would like to express my deepest apologies for any inconvenience caused.

I want to emphasize that this offense was not intentional. In all honesty, I genuinely believed that the bill had been paid. It was only after 8 months of unlicensed use that I realized my mistake. As soon as I became aware of the situation, I immediately rectified it by paying for a licence properly.

I want to bring to the court's attention that I have no previous criminal record. Throughout my life, I have always strived to uphold the law and be a law-abiding citizen. This incident is an anomaly in my otherwise clean record.

It is important for me to state that I am ready and willing to take any necessary steps to make this situation right. I understand the importance of fulfilling my obligations and ensuring that I comply with the law. I am committed to preventing any such offenses from happening again in the future.

I also want to express my sincere remorse for any inconvenience or frustration this may have caused to the relevant authorities. I assure you that it was never my intention to evade payment or disregard the law. I deeply regret the oversight that led to this situation.

In light of these circumstances, I kindly request the court to consider certain mitigating factors. Firstly, I emphasize that my guilty plea itself is a significant mitigating factor. By pleading guilty, I am acknowledging my wrongdoing and taking accountability for my actions.

Furthermore, I have already taken prompt action to rectify the situation and ensure compliance. This demonstrates my genuine commitment to righting any wrongs and preventing similar offenses from occurring in the future.

I understand that my offense may have caused inconvenience, but I plead with the court to take into account my clean record, my immediate actions to rectify the situation, and my sincere remorse.

In conclusion, I stand before this court ready to face the consequences of my actions. I am truly remorseful for the offense committed and I am committed to rectifying the situation and preventing any such incidents in the future. I humbly request the court's leniency and consideration in sentencing.

Thank you, Your Honor, for allowing me to address this court.
