As soon as I realized my mistake, I promptly rectified the situation and obtained a TV license, ensuring that I am now in compliance with the law. I want to emphasize that my guilty plea reflects my sincere acknowledgment of my mistake and my genuine remorse. By pleading guilty, I hope to demonstrate to the court my willingness to accept accountability.

I would like to bring to the court's attention that I have no previous criminal record, which attests to my commitment to abide by the law and fulfill my legal obligations. It serves as evidence of my character and dedication to being a responsible and law-abiding citizen. I assure the court that this incident is an isolated occurrence, and I have learned a valuable lesson from it.

In light of these circumstances, I fully accept the consequences of my actions and deeply apologize for any inconvenience caused. I respectfully request the court's understanding and leniency in considering the mitigation of my sentence. This incident has caused me great distress and I am hopeful that the court will take into account the extenuating circumstances and my previous track record of being a law-abiding citizen.

Thank you, Your Honor, for allowing me the opportunity to address the court and plead for your understanding.
